# TRADING DISCIPLINE PLATFORM

## Technical Requirements Document (TRD v2)

---

# 1. PRODUCT OVERVIEW

## 1.1 Objective

Build a trading platform that enforces disciplined execution by separating:

* Strategy Definition (thinking phase)
* Trade Execution (action phase)

The system must:

* Prevent impulsive trades
* Allow controlled bypass with accountability
* Track discipline independently from P&L
* Adapt to beginner and advanced users

---

# 2. CORE PRINCIPLES

1. Discipline over prediction
2. Friction over impulsivity
3. Transparency over black-box scoring
4. Flexibility with accountability (NOT freedom without consequences)

---

# 3. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE

## 3.1 High-Level Components

* Frontend (Web App)
* Backend API Layer
* Scoring Engine
* Discipline Engine
* Market Data Engine
* Cache Layer (Redis)
* Database (PostgreSQL)
* Async Workers (Queue-based)

---

## 3.2 Data Flow Model

Market Data → Processing Layer → Rule Engine → Score Cache → API → UI

---

# 4. USER MODES

## 4.1 Discipline Profiles

* Strict Mode

  * Hard rules block execution
  * Full friction on override

* Balanced Mode

  * Some hard rules degrade to warnings
  * Reduced friction

* Expert Mode

  * No blocking
  * Overrides always logged
  * Fast execution enabled

---

# 5. STRATEGY BUILDER

## 5.1 Strategy Object

```
Strategy {
  id: string
  name: string
  timeframe: string
  rules: Rule[]
  regimeCondition: RegimeRule
  disciplineProfile: string
  parentStrategyId?: string
  changeLog: string[]
}
```

---

## 5.2 Rule Types

### Hard Rules

* Block execution if failed (depending on mode)

### Soft Rules

* Affect score only

---

## 5.3 Rule Structure

```
Rule {
  id: string
  type: "simple" | "composite"
  metric: string
  operator: string
  value: number
  weight: number
  isHard: boolean
  conditions?: Rule[]
  logicalOperator?: "AND" | "OR"
}
```

---

## 5.4 Market Regime Rule

```
RegimeRule {
  symbol: "SPY"
  condition: string
  timeframe: string
}
```

---

# 6. COMPUTATION ENGINE

## 6.1 Execution Timing

| Rule Type     | Trigger      |
| ------------- | ------------ |
| Fundamentals  | Daily        |
| Regime        | Daily        |
| Technical     | Candle Close |
| Price Trigger | Real-time    |

---

## 6.2 Score Cache

```
CachedScore {
  ticker: string
  strategyId: string
  score: number
  hardRulePass: boolean
  lastUpdated: timestamp
}
```

---

## 6.3 Update Mechanism

* Pub/Sub model
* Event-driven recalculation

---

# 7. COMPATIBILITY ENGINE

## 7.1 Output

* Score (0–100)
* Hard rule status
* Rule breakdown

---

## 7.2 Evaluation Mode

Default: Closed candle
Optional (Expert): Live with tolerance buffer

---

## 7.3 Tolerance Buffer

```
ToleranceRule {
  metric: string
  bufferPercent: number
}
```

